NaI crystal (75*75 mm2) placed at an angle of
90 degrees to the beam direction was used to detect
gamma rays with Eg>3.5 and 6.5 MeV.
Germanium-Lithium detector with V=17 cm2
placed at an angle of 90 degrees to the beam
direction was used to detect gamma rays in the
resonance areas and between them.
The target of Ni-58 (enriched to 97.6%)with the
thickness of 2.5 keV was prepared by electric
precipitation on a thick backing.
Four Silicon-Lithium detectors with a resolution
of 25 keV were used.
Ni-58 foil (without backing) enriched to 99.7% with the
thickness of 3.8 keV was used for 5 MeV protons.
